**Available for Deployment!**

Our staff of dedicated tiny boffins had not sat idle and is proud to announce the latest and greatest in the tiny MBT scene - our new Apex MBT series. These high quality tanks are festooned with everything an enterprising tiny panzer general could ever desire. Elegant hull comes with two weapon option along with optional trench rails and engine filtration system for all your trench warfare needs! Equally as impressive is turret weaponry - of which 7 novel and brand new options are provided including:

- Standard cannon
- Extralong tank killer cannon
- Dual autocannon
- Dual laser cannon
- Siege howitzer
- Plasma projector
- Thermal ray emitter

All existing sponson weapon options are generously included.

Additional are provided for tiny tank connoisseurs. Furthermore, you will be glad to find our turret hatches completely operational (saber wielding psychopath not included).

Our long time fans will be delighted to know that this tank's turrets are fully interchangeable with the previous releases in tiny mbt family.

This vehicle is perfect for tiny combat in 6 to 8 mm scale!

Rumbling forward on heavy tracks, the tanks of the Imperial Army are capable of decimating enemy forces with overwhelming firepower. The versatile main battle tank is capable of being adapted to feature a wide range of alternate patterns - support vehicles capable of hauling damaged vehicles or artillery, hulls with sponsons, dozer blades and ram bars.

This is a single hull sample of a set of tank hulls featuring 8 base hull designs - The full set contains a Destroyer hull, Thunderer hull, Flamer hull, laser cannon hull, heavy bolt hull, automatic cannon hull, and two support variant hulls. Each of these come with bulldozer blade and ram bar options. Each of the standard tank hull designs also comes with options for two different sponson designs (square and inset versions) , with holes for magnetisation. Included in the main set are also two turret options, to create complete tanks. For a sample turret, please see my other designs.

This sample hull has been made to be compatible with 8mm scale main line battle tanks of the Imperial Army in a recently released 8mm grim-dark future wargame. They feature a magnet hole, and a peg compatible with existing plastic model turrets.

This sample is free. For the full set, I've priced it cheaply, but priced it as a reflection of the time I took to create such an extensive set. I deeply appreciate all those who support and encourage my work by buying any of my paid designs.

Please see my other items for a free sample of this set, and a range of other 8mm scale and other wargames and hobby models, including a set of compatible turret options for these tanks. I am an enthusiastic amateur designer, self and video-tutorial taught, so am always open to constructive feedback.

Please consider liking the design and posting a make.

An improved pattern of the M'khand Pattern Lemoine Russel Battle Tank, with improved suspension and internal layout offering more crew comfort and higher accuracy when firing on the move. Comes with all turret coxial and sponson weapon options offered at larger scales for maximum customisation.

Completed bodies, turrets and middles have 2.5x1.25mm holes for magnets. Compatible with all epic scale M'khand-pattern Lemoine Russel parts and variants. Comes with a variety of decals and effects.

The zip includes all my parts and meshmixer files. With Meshmixer (free program from Autodesk), simply Shift+Click the pieces you want to use and select export under the FILE dropdown menu. Alternatively, parts can be assembled via 3dBuilder, Blender or another software of your choice. Exported pieces are then ready for repair in netfab/3dbuilder/prusaslicer and slicing.

For best results when printing destroyed turrets, include a closed hatch with the turret, weapon and smoke to prevent a small pocket of unprinted resin.

__For printing for LIMP/AT18, increase scale to 125% when slicing__

2023-12-03: Added new options for side weapons and a builder with all my other lemoine russel variants in it.

2023-12-07: Added adapters to fit the turrets to plastic LIMP hulls. Combine with other wanted parts before scaling up 125%

2023-12-07: Split hull weapon mounts from the hulls. Added new hull weapon options. Removed the old redundant builder file.

2024-01-14: Added coronal-designations of the three patterns of turret as well as both a turret-mounted heat ray and heavy flamethrower.

2024-08-24: Added internal side sponsons.

Stroganoff made some beautiful Leman Russ models in 6mm for games like Epic. That's great and all, but a 10 Russ company has 9 Main Battle Tanks, and one Vanquisher in NetEA. And then there's the Demolishers you can attach in 3s. What's a gamer to do?

Make them!

Here you will find some variant turrets for Leman Russ chassis tanks. Demolisher, Vanquisher, Punisher, Conqueror, Executioner, Eradicator, Exterminator (come on GeeDubs, those names are just confusing) The Exterminator could double as an Annihilator.

There are two Punisher turrets. A 6 barrel and a 4 barrel. The 4 prints cleaner, but the 6 did not feel as flimsy to me. So your milage may vary there. Could have been my post-processing.

These have been printed on an SLA printer. Some of these items are not going to print well on an FDM printer. The Punisher and Exterminator come to mind. I might edit the Eradicator a little as it has little supports on the side which might be too thin/separated from the main barrel. It won't really affect printing, but might not form well in the process.
